---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { u } from '../../lib/url';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How we work — Thorn"
  description="The principles behind every Thorn engagement. Plain pricing, named accountability, no fragmented contracts, no kickbacks, no surprises."
  lang="en"
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="surface-light pt-12 md:pt-20 pb-16 md:pb-24">
    <div class="container-page">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-y-8 md:gap-x-10">
        <div class="md:col-span-9">
          <div class="eyebrow text-forest-700 mb-8 md:mb-10">
            <span class="font-mono">001</span>
            <span class="mx-3 text-ink-300">·</span>
            How we work
          </div>
          <h1 class="font-sans font-medium text-display-1 text-ink-900 hang tracking-tight">
            The principles<br/>
            <span class="text-ink-400">every engagement runs on.</span>
          </h1>
        </div>

        <aside class="md:col-span-3 md:pt-32 md:border-l md:border-forest-100 md:pl-6">
          <div class="eyebrow text-ink-500 mb-3">Count</div>
          <div class="font-mono tabular text-ink-900 text-body-sm mb-6">08 / 08</div>

          <div class="eyebrow text-ink-500 mb-3">Status</div>
          <div class="text-ink-900 text-body-sm mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Operating rules,<br/>not aspirations
          </div>

          <div class="eyebrow text-ink-500 mb-3">If we can't honour</div>
          <div class="text-ink-900 text-body-sm leading-relaxed">
            We say so<br/>before signing
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 md:mt-16 max-w-2xl">
        <p class="text-body-lg text-ink-700 leading-relaxed">
          These are not aspirations. They're operating rules. If we can't honour them on a particular engagement, we say so before signing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Principles -->
  <section class="surface-medium section">
    <div class="container-page">
      <div class="max-w-5xl space-y-12 md:space-y-16">

        <article class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 md:gap-10 pb-12 md:pb-16 border-b border-forest-100">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <div class="step-numeral-lg">01</div>
            <div class="eyebrow text-forest-700 mt-4">Pricing</div>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-2xl md:text-[28px] text-ink-900 mb-4 leading-tight tracking-tight">
              Plain pricing, published ranges
            </h3>
            <p class="text-ink-700 text-body leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
              Our service pages name the price ranges for every offer. No bespoke quotes hidden until page 40 of a proposal. When we send you a fixed-fee proposal, the numbers will sit inside the published ranges or we'll tell you upfront why this engagement is an exception.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 md:gap-10 pb-12 md:pb-16 border-b border-forest-100">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <div class="step-numeral-lg">02</div>
            <div class="eyebrow text-forest-700 mt-4">Accountability</div>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-2xl md:text-[28px] text-ink-900 mb-4 leading-tight tracking-tight">
              Named accountability, end to end
            </h3>
            <p class="text-ink-700 text-body leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
              Every engagement has one technical lead. They sign the proposal. They run the discovery. They show up on site. They stay on the project from kickoff to handover. We don't sell you to one team and subcontract delivery to another.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 md:gap-10 pb-12 md:pb-16 border-b border-forest-100">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <div class="step-numeral-lg">03</div>
            <div class="eyebrow text-forest-700 mt-4">Contracts</div>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-2xl md:text-[28px] text-ink-900 mb-4 leading-tight tracking-tight">
              No fragmented contracts
            </h3>
            <p class="text-ink-700 text-body leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
              Article 11 of Law 98/2016 forbids splitting contracts to dodge procurement thresholds. We won't propose it. If your scope is larger than one threshold, we run the right SEAP procedure for the right size. It takes a few weeks longer. It stays clean.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 md:gap-10 pb-12 md:pb-16 border-b border-forest-100">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <div class="step-numeral-lg">04</div>
            <div class="eyebrow text-rust-500 mt-4">Red line</div>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-2xl md:text-[28px] text-ink-900 mb-4 leading-tight tracking-tight">
              No kickbacks. No pre-decided tenders.
            </h3>
            <p class="text-ink-700 text-body leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
              We don't pay to win contracts. We don't participate in tenders that have been decided in advance. If a procurement looks engineered for a specific vendor, we either flag it to ANAP or walk away. This is a hard line, not a slogan.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 md:gap-10 pb-12 md:pb-16 border-b border-forest-100">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <div class="step-numeral-lg">05</div>
            <div class="eyebrow text-forest-700 mt-4">Ownership</div>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-2xl md:text-[28px] text-ink-900 mb-4 leading-tight tracking-tight">
              Open standards, your data stays yours
            </h3>
            <p class="text-ink-700 text-body leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
              Open formats, exportable schemas, no vendor lock-in clauses. If you ever decide to migrate away from us, we hand you everything that's yours. Code, data, infrastructure-as-code, runbooks. The kind of handover we'd want if we were on your side of the table.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 md:gap-10 pb-12 md:pb-16 border-b border-forest-100">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <div class="step-numeral-lg">06</div>
            <div class="eyebrow text-forest-700 mt-4">Residency</div>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-2xl md:text-[28px] text-ink-900 mb-4 leading-tight tracking-tight">
              Romanian data residency by default
            </h3>
            <p class="text-ink-700 text-body leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
              Public-sector data layers run on Romanian infrastructure (Romarg, ClausWeb). Where compute can sit elsewhere without exposing data, we use efficient EU providers (Hetzner) and tell you exactly where each component lives. No mystery, no offshore surprises.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 md:gap-10 pb-12 md:pb-16 border-b border-forest-100">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <div class="step-numeral-lg">07</div>
            <div class="eyebrow text-forest-700 mt-4">Honesty</div>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-2xl md:text-[28px] text-ink-900 mb-4 leading-tight tracking-tight">
              We say what we won't do
            </h3>
            <p class="text-ink-700 text-body leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
              Each service page has a "what we don't do" section. It's not false modesty. It's the fastest way to make sure both sides know what they're buying. If your problem is outside our scope, we tell you on the first call and, where we can, point you to someone better suited.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 md:gap-10">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <div class="step-numeral-lg">08</div>
            <div class="eyebrow text-forest-700 mt-4">Documentation</div>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <h3 class="font-sans font-semibold text-2xl md:text-[28px] text-ink-900 mb-4 leading-tight tracking-tight">
              Documentation as deliverable
            </h3>
            <p class="text-ink-700 text-body leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
              Every engagement ships with written documentation: architecture, runbooks, decision log, handover notes. Not because it's nice to have, but because the next person to touch this system needs to understand it without us in the room.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="surface-light section">
    <div class="container-page text-center">
      <div class="eyebrow text-forest-700 mb-6">002</div>
      <h2 class="font-sans font-medium text-display-2 text-ink-900 leading-tight mb-10 hang max-w-2xl mx-auto tracking-tight">
        These principles<br/>sound like a fit?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-body-lg text-ink-700 max-w-xl mx-auto mb-12">
        Then a conversation is probably worth thirty minutes. Tell us what you're working on.
      </p>
      <a href={u('/en/contact')} class="btn-primary">
        Start a conversation
        <svg class="btn-arrow" width="14" height="10" viewBox="0 0 14 10" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M0 5h12M8 1l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
